<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1457">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/156.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General.</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Villa has placed million Mexican dollars fine on Chamber of
                            Commerce. Applies to foreigners in Mexico. I shall oppose forcing
                            Americans and other foreigners paying such fine or forced contributions.
                            Please instruct me as it will help case.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>